<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="568" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,531,1328,1391]" box="[151,531,1328,1355]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,531,1328,1355]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,531,1328,1355]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
Key to species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Priesner" authorityYear="1938" box="[366,531,1328,1355]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Lefroyothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[366,531,1328,1355]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Lefroyothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,531,1328,1391]" box="[151,377,1364,1391]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">[* from description]</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="568" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1433,1983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
1. Fore wing dark at apex, with one shaded band medially and the second at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1002,1074,1433,1456]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–23" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,453,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-157@6.[152,1436,453,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–23. Lefroyothrips species. Female tergites VII–X, 17–19: (17) lefroyi; (18) pictus; (19) tribulationi. male tergite IX, 20–21: (20) pictus; (21) fasciatus. (22) lefroyi female sternites VI–VII. (23) fasciatus fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543161" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543161/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
); sternite VII of female with setae S2 arising at margin; male without sternal pore plates........................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1433,1983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="568">-. Fore wing pale at apex, with shaded bands near veinal fork and on distal third sub-apically; some species with sternite VII setae S2 of female arising in front of margin; sternal pore plates present on males (where known).......................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1433,1983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
2. Abdominal tergites II and VII dark brown, much darker than I and III–VI; segments VIII–X variably brownish yellow to medium brown.................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moulton" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[1351,1436,1580,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Lefroyothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciatus">
<emphasis box="[1351,1436,1580,1601]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">fasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1433,1983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
-. Abdominal tergites mainly brown, but I and V yellow, VIII sharply yellow on posterior half, IX with a narrow yellow band at anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[387,456,1639,1661]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–23" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,453,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-157@6.[152,1436,453,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–23. Lefroyothrips species. Female tergites VII–X, 17–19: (17) lefroyi; (18) pictus; (19) tribulationi. male tergite IX, 20–21: (20) pictus; (21) fasciatus. (22) lefroyi female sternites VI–VII. (23) fasciatus fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543161" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543161/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
)........................................................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1379,1436,1639,1660]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Lefroyothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis box="[1379,1436,1639,1660]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1433,1983]" box="[151,1437,1668,1690]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<keyLead box="[151,1437,1668,1690]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
3. Ocellar setae pair III 80 microns long; body uniformly brown, tergites darker on anterior halves................ * 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ananthakrishnan &amp; Jagadish" authorityYear="1966" box="[1350,1437,1668,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Taeniothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscurus">
<emphasis box="[1350,1437,1668,1689]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">obscurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1433,1983]" box="[151,1436,1697,1719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1697,1719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">-. Ocellar setae pair III less than 50 microns; body extensively pale............................................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1433,1983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
4. Ocellar setae pair III very small (
<figureCitation box="[547,605,1727,1749]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,417,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1435,417,1909]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Lefroyothrips species. Antennal segments, 1–6: (1) fasciatus holotype; (2) fasciatus male; (3) lefroyi; (4) pictus paratype; (5) tribulationi; (6) varatharajani. 7–8 lefroyi: (7) female; (8) head &amp; pronotum. L. tribulationi, 9–10: (9) head; (10) pronotum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543157" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543157/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
), shorter than length of a posterior ocellus, and no longer than postocular setae pair I; postocular setae in an irregular pair of rows [sternite VII posteromarginal setae S2 usually sub-marginal in origin (
<figureCitation box="[1323,1395,1755,1778]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–23" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,453,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-157@6.[152,1436,453,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–23. Lefroyothrips species. Female tergites VII–X, 17–19: (17) lefroyi; (18) pictus; (19) tribulationi. male tergite IX, 20–21: (20) pictus; (21) fasciatus. (22) lefroyi female sternites VI–VII. (23) fasciatus fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543161" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543161/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
)]................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName box="[1374,1436,1785,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Physothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lefroyi">
<emphasis box="[1374,1436,1785,1806]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">lefroyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1433,1983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
-. Ocellar setae III longer, at least twice as long as postocular setae I (
<figureCitation box="[869,931,1815,1837]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,417,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1435,417,1909]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Lefroyothrips species. Antennal segments, 1–6: (1) fasciatus holotype; (2) fasciatus male; (3) lefroyi; (4) pictus paratype; (5) tribulationi; (6) varatharajani. 7–8 lefroyi: (7) female; (8) head &amp; pronotum. L. tribulationi, 9–10: (9) head; (10) pronotum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543157" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543157/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Figs 9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[941,968,1815,1837]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–27" captionStartId="7.[151,264,808,832]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,783]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[151,1435,181,783]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 24–27. Lefroyothrips species. L. varatharajani 24–26: (24) head; (25) male tergites VIII–IX; (26) male sternites. (27) L. lefroyi male sternites." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543163" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543163/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">24</figureCitation>
); postocular setae arranged in a single transverse row................................................................................................ 5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1433,1983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
5. All antennal segments dark, III with base and apex sharply pale (
<figureCitation box="[869,929,1873,1895]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,417,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1435,417,1909]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Lefroyothrips species. Antennal segments, 1–6: (1) fasciatus holotype; (2) fasciatus male; (3) lefroyi; (4) pictus paratype; (5) tribulationi; (6) varatharajani. 7–8 lefroyi: (7) female; (8) head &amp; pronotum. L. tribulationi, 9–10: (9) head; (10) pronotum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543157" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543157/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); metanotal median setae arise well behind anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[307,377,1903,1925]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–16" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1463,1487]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,452,1439]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[151,1435,452,1439]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11–16. Lefroyothrips species—metascutum. (11) fasciatus holotype; (12) fasciatus paratype male; (13) fasciatus male; (14) lefroyi; (15) tribulationi; (16) varatharajani." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543159/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); sternite VII setae S2 arise well in front of posterior margin......................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Mound &amp; Ng, 2021" authorityName="Mound &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2021" box="[1273,1382,1903,1924]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Lefroyothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tribulationi" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis box="[1273,1382,1903,1924]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">tribulationi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1388,1436,1903,1924]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1388,1430,1903,1924]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">sp.n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1433,1983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
-. At least antennal segment III pale (
<figureCitation box="[560,619,1932,1954]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,417,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1435,417,1909]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Lefroyothrips species. Antennal segments, 1–6: (1) fasciatus holotype; (2) fasciatus male; (3) lefroyi; (4) pictus paratype; (5) tribulationi; (6) varatharajani. 7–8 lefroyi: (7) female; (8) head &amp; pronotum. L. tribulationi, 9–10: (9) head; (10) pronotum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543157" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543157/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); metanotal median setae arise at anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1102,1173,1932,1954]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–16" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1463,1487]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,452,1439]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[151,1435,452,1439]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11–16. Lefroyothrips species—metascutum. (11) fasciatus holotype; (12) fasciatus paratype male; (13) fasciatus male; (14) lefroyi; (15) tribulationi; (16) varatharajani." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543159/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); sternite VII setae S2 arise at posterior margin.......................................................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1303,1436,1961,1982]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Lefroyothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varatharajani">
<emphasis box="[1303,1436,1961,1982]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">varatharajani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</subSubSection>
